Perhaps it would be fitting out-of-universe, but given that Japanese is only spoken natively on one chain of islands that purposely kept itself isolated from the rest of the world for centuries, it wouldn't make sense for it to become a lingua franca for the world if English never existed, nor would it be likely that the SCP Foundation's main branch would be in Japan.







