19 Oct 2018 14:39






It's not the most likely candidate, but the effects of removing England from history would be so far-reaching predicting the plausibility of different alternate histories would be meaningless (especially as English as a global lingua franca is heavily influenced by the USA, which would be completely unrecognisable in this situation). I don't think Japan would rise to global domination, but I could easily envision a world where there is no commonly accepted global language, and Japanese would be highly influential - without the USA, Japan is the world's second largest economy, so I don't see why the Foundation-equivalent's main branch couldn't be there. I could easily suspend my disbelief here for artistic yields, anyway.







